    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Creating physical distance between yourself and your device during meaningful activities improves focus and demonstrates respect for the people and experiences in front of you. Choose a consistent location like a basket by the front door, a drawer, or a specific table where you place your phone during meals, conversations, work sessions, or quality time with loved ones. This visible commitment to presence helps break the unconscious habit of reaching for your device and signals to others that you value undivided attention in your relationships and activities.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-43',
    prompt: 'Install and configure a digital wellness tracking app to monitor your screen time reduction progress',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Measuring your progress with concrete data helps maintain motivation and identify patterns in your digital usage throughout your detox journey. Choose apps like RescueTime, Moment, or your device\'s built-in screen time tools to track daily usage across different apps and categories. Set up weekly progress reports and establish specific reduction targets (like decreasing social media time by 30 minutes per week) to create measurable goals. This objective feedback loop prevents you from underestimating usage and provides positive reinforcement when you successfully reduce your digital consumption.'
  }
];</parameter>
